node.text: Porsche is in the minds of many the ultimate sports car brand. Its cars – especially its legendary 911 – blend high performance with quality construction and even a solid reputation for dependability. But the brand that made its name with small nimble two-door sports cars ruffled feathers in the automotive world when it tried its hand at a four-door sport utility vehicle, the Cayenne. Today, SUVs make up a huge chunk of Porsche’s sales. The brand is now entering the race toward electrification – but this time the innovator is playing catch-up to others.

node.title: How Porsche went from sports cars to SUVs ... and EVs

node.text: It’s taken over two years, but these days Jeremy Mateo is finally feeling at home. Mateo, 27, is a real estate broker in Honolulu, Hawaii, and bought his first condo on Oahu island right before the coronavirus pandemic in March 2020. Over the course of a year he saved $60,000 for a down payment and worked toward his goal of buying his “dream home.” Then he spent another year renovating and furnishing his place. The last of his furniture arrived in spring 2021, finally closing the chapter on his homebuying journey. Here’s how Mateo bought his one-bedroom condo for $560,000. (With @CNBCMakeIt)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 20, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and text that says 'Tesla will build a humanoid robot prototype by next year, Elon Musk says CNBC'.

node.text:
Tesla will build a humanoid robot called Tesla Bot, CEO Elon Musk said on Thursday. 🤖⁠
⁠
“We’re also good at sensors and batteries and we’ll probably have a prototype next year that looks like this,” Musk said, shortly after an actor in a body suit designed to look like the Tesla robot gyrated wildly on stage. He remarked that the actor was not a real robot, but “the Tesla Bot will be real.”⁠
⁠
What exactly does Musk envision the Tesla Bot to be able to do? Link in bio.

May be an image of map and text that says 'This map shows where cryptocurrency is taking off around the world Countries are scored on scale of Oto1. 0.1 0.2 0.3 0.4 Jordan Index score: 0.03 Vietnam, score of 1 is the only country above 0.4 Source: Chainalysis. Only includes countries listed in the Chainalysis index. CNBC'.

node.text:
Global adoption of cryptocurrency has taken off in the last year, up 881%, with Vietnam, India and Pakistan firmly in the lead, according to new data from Chainalysis.⁠
⁠
Most of the top 20 countries are emerging economies, including Togo, Colombia and Afghanistan. Meanwhile, the United States slipped from sixth to eighth place, and China, which cracked down on crypto this spring, dropped from fourth to 13th.⁠
⁠
Which other countries ranked at the top of the list? Link in bio to find out.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 19, 2021. May be an image of car and text that says 'Tesla buyers confounded by delivery delays stretching for months REIMAGINE. UDIO MODELS TESLA 1 MOOF CNBC'.

node.text:
Some Tesla customers in Florida and California have experienced delivery delays of weeks or months, forcing them to rely on borrowed cars, costly rentals and ride-hailing apps while they weather the unexpected wait.⁠
⁠
Tesla acknowledged Model S delays earlier this year, but the delivery issues extend to the Model Y, Tesla’s crossover SUV and most popular vehicle in North America, according to several customers who spoke to CNBC.⁠
⁠
In 2018 Elon Musk referenced Tesla was struggling with “delivery logistics hell." Details on how the continuing delays are a sign the company is still experiencing that at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Facebook launched a VR remote work app- here's what it is like CNBC'.

node.text:
Remote work is going VR.⁠
⁠
Facebook on Thursday announced Horizon Workrooms, a new way for office workers to connect using virtual reality.⁠
⁠
The idea is simple enough: Instead of talking to people in little boxes over video calls, Facebook spent more than two years creating a way for up to 16 people, represented by avatars, to sit around a virtual conference table together. It supports up to 50 people if some just call in using webcams.⁠
⁠
Interested in seeing what Facebook Workrooms looks like in VR? Check out some more photos at the link in bio. 📸

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Amazon is reportedly planning to open department stores amazon CNBC'.

node.text:
This is Amazon's latest move into physical retail. 👀⁠
⁠
Amazon is planning to open large retail locations that resemble department stores, The Wall Street Journal reported.⁠
⁠
The newspaper reported that some of the first Amazon department stores are expected to be in California and Ohio. The locations will take up roughly 30,000 square feet, around the size of a Kohl’s or T.J. Maxx store.⁠
⁠
The e-commerce site recently overtook Walmart as the world’s largest retail seller outside of China. So, why the move into brick and mortar? Link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 18, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'China calls for curbs on "excessive" income and for the wealthy to give back more to society CNBC'.

node.text:
Chinese President Xi Jinping emphasized at a finance and economic meeting Tuesday the need to support moderate wealth for all — or the idea of “common prosperity,” which analysts have said is behind the latest regulatory crackdown on tech companies. ⁠
⁠
The meeting called for the “reasonable adjustment of excessive incomes and encouraging high income groups and businesses to return more to society,” state media said in Chinese, according to a CNBC translation.⁠
⁠
Details on how much income inequality among China’s 1.4 billion people has increased over the years at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 18, 2021. May be an image of money.

node.text:
Robinhood 🤝 Crypto⁠
⁠
Robinhood said its crypto revenue accounted for more than half of all transaction-based revenue in the second quarter, as retail investors turned to the app for purchases of bitcoin, ethereum and other digital currencies.⁠
⁠
In its first earnings report since its IPO last month, Robinhood said its revenue from crypto transactions was $233 million, up from $5 million in the year-ago quarter. ⁠
⁠
What percentage of cumulative net-funded accounts traded crypto in the quarter? Link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'U.S. will begin wide distribution of Covid booster shots next month, saying vaccine protection wanes over time CNBC'.

node.text:
🚨 BREAKING. 🚨⁠
⁠
The U.S. will begin widely distributing Covid-19 booster shots next month as new data shows that vaccine protection wanes over time, top U.S. health officials announced in a joint statement Wednesday.⁠
⁠
U.S. agencies are preparing to offer booster shots to all eligible Americans beginning the week of Sept. 20, starting 8 months after their second dose of Pfizer or Moderna’s vaccines, officials said. While they said recipients of Johnson & Johnson’s single-shot vaccine will likely need boosters, they are awaiting more data in the next few weeks before making a formal recommendation.⁠
⁠
More details on the decision to recommend booster shots at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 18, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'to Investors are starting question whether there really is no alternative to the u.s., BofA finds BOBBY CNBC'.

node.text:
New for subscribers: The notion that the U.S. is practically the only place to invest is intact among professional investors who nonetheless are starting to get concerned about some issues that could derail that trade.⁠
⁠
Respondents to August’s Bank of America Fund Manager Survey are still loaded up on stocks, though they cut allocations by 4 percentage points to a net 54% overweight position, the lowest since July 2020.⁠
⁠
Why do many investors think there is no alternative to U.S. equities? Read more at the link in bio. (Check out CNBC Pro for 7 days for free!)

node.text:
The “Super Bowl” of classic car collecting ended with a roar over the weekend, with auction sales at Monterey and Pebble Beach totaling $345 million, up 35% from 2019.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
The top seller of the week, as expected, was a 1995 McLaren F1 sold by Gooding & Co. for $20.5 million, making it the most expensive car to sell at auction since 2018.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
For details on the top 10 cars sold during Monterey Car Week (and how much they sold for), visit the link in bio.

node.text:
The cryptocurrency platform targeted in a massive heist is now inviting the hacker behind it to become an advisor to the firm, and promising a $500,000 reward for the restoration of user funds.⁠
⁠
Poly Network was hit with a major attack last week which saw the hacker, or hackers, make off with more than $600 million worth of tokens. It is thought to be the largest crypto heist of all time. In Poly Network’s case, the hacker has taken the unusual step of returning most of the stolen money. All but $33 million of the crypto has now been returned. ⁠
⁠
Details on if that hacker (dubbed "Mr. White Hat") plans to accept Poly Network's offer at the link in bio.
